snippet.textDisplay: All to easy , the Wembley losers huddle clearly did nothing . At the end of the day we have been awful all season . The manager has to take the blame , we have some of the worst premier league stas ever ! We are defensively clueless , worse defence in can remember for 20 years . Not player for player but the total cluelessness that is occurring . Smith has no plan b , his tactics have been poor , his game management has been poor , his man management has been poor and his recruitment has been poor if we are going on performances. We live the fact smith is a villa fan and manages our club ...... BUT ........ his job is to win matches , make us competitive and keep us in the premier league . He's failed miserably . I like Dean smith as a man as a fellow fan but he is out of his depth . A decision was made to give him a new 4 year contract so I guess the plan is to keep him regardless of what happens . A mistake by the club in my opinion . There's no point sacking him now , what good would that do ? Nobody is out there , who would touch villa right now ? And as for McGinn being the saviour ? To little to late , smith shouldn't of run him into the ground in the first place as that's back fired on him . It's a sad time to be a villa fan and watch our beloved club sink into the championship tactically clueless and being embarrassed .

snippet.textDisplay:
Mings did touch it with his shoulder, no penalty.

VAR is turning more and more into a joke to be honest when you look at this. Refs make calls just to be on the safe side thinking there's someone watching a monitor. Then VAR says "yeah, whatever the ref called" though it clearly isn't, just because they don't want to dent the image/authority of the ref on field.

Let the ref take responsibility as if there's no VAR and allow captain of the team have 3 VAR requests over the game for plays he considers problematic.
